parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Fuel Leak and Strong Fuel Smell
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The fuel leak and strong fuel smell can cause a fire hazard, health risks, and reduced visibility due to condensation on the windshield.
symptoms: Strong fuel smell inside the cabin
fuel leaks onto the engine block
fuel smell persists even after driving
and condensation on the windshield.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the ABS system on rough surfaces can cause extended braking distances, loss of brake pedal pressure, and increased stopping times, leading to accidents or near-misses.
symptoms: The ABS system engages unnecessarily on rough surfaces
such as potholes
railroad tracks
or rippled roads
causing the brake pedal to go to the floor or reducing braking effectiveness.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Brake Pedal Sinking or Soft Pedal
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The brake pedal sinking or feeling soft can cause a loss of braking power, leading to accidents or near-misses.
symptoms: The brake pedal feels soft or spongy
or sinks to the floor when pressed
reducing braking effectiveness.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Ineffective Braking on Wet or Slippery Surfaces
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Ineffective braking on wet or slippery surfaces can cause accidents or near-misses, especially when approaching turns or intersections.
symptoms: The vehicle fails to brake effectively on wet
snowy
or icy surfaces
causing the vehicle to slide or lose control.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Fuel Leak and Gasoline Odor in Cold Weather
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The fuel leak and gasoline odor in cold weather can cause a significant safety hazard, as it can lead to a fire in the engine compartment or cabin, potentially resulting in injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: Strong smell of gasoline or fuel in the cabin
engine compartment
or outside the vehicle
especially in cold weather; fuel puddles on top of the engine; nausea
dizziness
or headaches due to fuel fumes; smell of gasoline or fuel when using the heater or defroster.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The inadequate repair by the dealership can lead to the continued presence of a safety hazard, as the fuel leak and gasoline odor may not be properly addressed, potentially resulting in injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: Dealership unable to replicate the problem or diagnose the issue; dealership claims that the problem is not present or is not a safety concern; inadequate repair or temporary fix that does not address the underlying issue.
